                  <additions>
                  <list>
                  <item xml:id="a01">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#iiv(erso) #iiir(ecto)"/> The nine feast days of Our Lord and the Apostles’ feast days, in faded ink
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="a02">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#ivv(erso)"/> Beginning of <title type="incomplete" ref="LIT1693John"/>
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="a03">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#168v"/> The Lucky and Unlucky Days of the Year, in a very clear hand.
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐሳበ፡ ጽንዕት፡ ወጽንጽንት፡ መሥከረም፡ እስከ፡ ፲፭፡ ጸንዕት፡ የቀረው፡ ጽንጽንት። ጥቅምት፡ እስከ፡ ፲፫፡ ጽንዕት፡ የቀረው፡ ጽንጽንት፡...</foreign>
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="a04">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#iir(ecto)"/> a couple of words
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e01">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #iiiv(erso)"/>: blank
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e02">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#39v"/>: washed of text, which is still faintly visible, to prepare for painting
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e03">
                  <desc>
                    <locus target="#63v"/> cross-shaped symbol in right margin, marks the midpoint of the psalms
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e04">
                  <desc>
                    Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e05">
                  <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 2–14
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e06">
                  <desc>
                    words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#5v #34v #39r #50v #55v"/>, etc.);
                    and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#3v #6v #9r #10v #16r"/>, etc.);
                    and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#143v"/>, line 15), and in another case where the symbol (┴) is used (<locus target="#157r"/>, line 1)
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e07">
                  <desc>
                    This scribe has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves ample room for the width of most lines. On a few occasions,
                    the line would have been too long and the scribe finishes the end of the line with words written smaller so as to avoid leftover text (e.g., <locus target="#42v #55v #100r"/>).
                    Occasionally a line is still too long and has to be completed above or below the end of the line (e.g., <locus target="#20r #40r #46r #60v"/>).
                  </desc>
                  </item>

                  </list>
